purposes.NOTES:
Refer to licence: Licensed quantity all year. However, summer abstraction is subject to compensatory discharges under further condition 9.2.
MXM: 5 mobile pumps to be measured by meter. 1 Archimedes pump to be measured by calculation of the hours of operation multiplied by the defined output of the pump.

purposePoints.NOTES: 5 mobile pumps and 1 fixed Archimedes' screw pump

point_detail.LOCAL_NAME: INLAND WATER DITCHES AND DRAINS KNWON AS THE LIPWELL STREAM
point_detail.LOCATION_TEXT: Northward Hill RSPB Reserve at Cooling, Rochester

point_source.NAME: Southern Region Surface Waters
point_source.NOTES: All Rivers, Streams and Lakes in Southern Region

licenceConditions.TEXT: From 1 November to 31 March inclusive: When annual abstraction from the first day of November in any year exceeds 22,730 cubic metres, no abstraction shall take place unless the level of water in the Lipwell Stream as measured at TQ 77316 76838 is equal to or greater than 1.25 AOD (equivalent of 1.10 metres depth).

From 1 April to 31 October inclusive: No water shall be abstracted unless a simultaneous compensatory discharge of water equal to the abstraction quantity is made from the off line reservoirs outlined in blue on the map into the drains outlined in red on the map and the compensatory discharge is completed that day.

For the means of abstraction specified in condition 3.1: 
From 1 November to 31 March inclusive: The Licence Holder shall take and record readings of the meter specified in condition 7.1 at the same time each week during the whole of the period during which abstraction is authorised or as otherwise approved in writing by the Agency.
From 1 April to 31 October inclusive: The Licence Holder shall take and record readings of the meter specified in condition 7.1 at the same time each day during the whole of the period during which abstraction is authorised or as otherwise approved in writing by the Agency.

(i) No abstraction using the means of abstraction specified in condition 3.2 shall take place until the operating capacity of it has been calibrated and calculated by an accredited company/organisation, and the Licence Holder has submitted the certification of calibration to the Agency for written approval. (ii) The Licence Holder shall maintain the equipment installed and used under condition 3.2, and shall calibrate the equipment regularly, in accordance with the recommendations of the manufacturer, and shall replace such equipment as necessary. The Licence Holder shall retain evidence of current and subsequent certifications of calibration for inspection by the Agency.

For the means of abstraction specified in condition 3.2: (i) The quantity of water abstracted shall be measured by the number of hours of operation of the pump multiplied by the defined output of the pump in one hour. (ii) The Licence Holder shall retain all supporting documentation, including certification details of the pump and which enables the defined output, flow rate and volume in time to be calculated.

For the means of abstraction specified in condition 3.2: Records of the hours of operation of the pump together with the corresponding quantity calculated by the means specified in condition 7.2 above shall be taken and recorded by the Licence Holder at the same time each day during the whole of the period during which abstraction is authorised or as otherwise approved in writing by the Agency. The Licence Holder shall take and record separate readings of quantities abstracted for; (i) filling reservoirs between 1 November to 31 March inclusive; (ii) supply to a wetland between 1 November to 31 March inclusive; (iii) subsequent discharge from the reservoirs between 1 April to 31 October inclusive, and; (iv) re-abstraction for supply to a wetland between 1 April to 31 October inclusive. The Licence Holder shall send a copy of the records required by conditions 8.1, 8.2 and 8.3 or summary data to the Agency within 28 calendar days of 31 March of each year or within 28 days of being so requested in writing by the Agency.
Each record shall be kept and be made available during all reasonable hours for inspection by the Agency for at least 6 years.

purposes.NOTES: Purpose 4.1(i) Transfer for the purpose of supply to a wetland
